There was one story from /x/ where some teenagers were driving through a rural area going to some late night party in another town and in the middle of nowhere saw a woman walking by the road, slowed down to ask her if she wants a ride, then saw she had goat hoofs and sped away.
Who remembers playing Mann Manor on Halloween as a kid?

It looked like a regular girl, but instead of feet she just had goat hoofs like the animal, you can imagine it. I think the idea was that OP thought they saw the devil. He's supposed to be roaming the earth after all. Very old school paranormal story.
I think he did, he definitely has the sinister look that you would associate with this stuff

I really like the concept of the "Day of the Dead". You have the normal Halloween with the dinner party costumes and horror movies and stuff and then on the next day you have a second, more esoteric Mexican Halloween.
Every holiday should be followed by a secret Mexican version of it celebrated on the following day.
